fields.title: Missing Person
fields.description: The missing person was reported by the victim’s husband, Logan Killicks. Mr. Killicks said that he and his wife had a fight about her role as a wife, his expectations, and her role as a field hand on his farm. Just before she goes missing, Mr. Killicks says that he calls her spoiled and belittles her. Mr. Killicks said that shortly after this fight. Janie disappeared between the hours of 9:00 and 10:00 a.m. eastern standard time on June 3 and has been missing for approximately two days. Janie was described as an Negro female of mixed-race with long black hair that falls down to her waist. She has fair skin with brown eyes. She is approximately five-foot and five inches in height and has brown eyes. Janie Crawford was last seen wearing a white shirt, denim overalls, and brown shoes. Janie does not appear to have any scars, tattoos, or noticeable birth marks.
